></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Defs.html#Algebra\">Algebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Localization/FractionRing.html#IsFractionRing\">IsFractionRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> (max u_2 u_2 u_1)</div></div>","info":{"doc":"`AdeleRing (𝓞 K) K` is the adele ring of a number field `K`.\n\nMore generally `AdeleRing R K` can be used if `K` is the field of fractions\nof the Dedekind domain `R`. This enables use of rings like `AdeleRing ℤ ℚ`, which\nin practice are easier to work with than `AdeleRing (𝓞 ℚ) ℚ`.\n\nNote that this definition does not give the correct answer in the function field case.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/NumberField/AdeleRing.html#NumberField.AdeleRing","kind":"def","line":39,"name":"NumberField.AdeleRing","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/NumberTheory/NumberField/AdeleRing.lean#L39-L48"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.NumberTheory.NumberField.InfiniteAdeleRing","Mathlib.RingTheory.DedekindDomain.FiniteAdeleRing"],"instances":[{"className":"CommRing","name":"NumberField.AdeleRing.instCommRing","typeNames":["NumberField.AdeleRing"]},{"className":"Inhabited","name":"NumberField.AdeleRing.instInhabited","typeNames":["NumberField.AdeleRing"]},{"className":"TopologicalSpace","name":"NumberField.AdeleRing.instTopologicalSpace","typeNames":["NumberField.AdeleRing"]},{"className":"IsTopologicalRing","name":"NumberField.AdeleRing.instIsTopologicalRing","typeNames":["NumberField.AdeleRing"]},{"className":"Algebra","name":"NumberField.AdeleRing.instAlgebra","typeNames":["NumberField.AdeleRing"]}],"name":"Mathlib.NumberTheory.NumberField.AdeleRing"}